{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":792,"text":"We're seen as the organization that is\nthe bucket for failed social policy."},{"time":4485,"text":"I can't define who comes to us or how long they stay."},{"time":7767,"text":"We get the people for whom\nnothing else has worked,"},{"time":9903,"text":"people who have fallen through all"},{"time":11341,"text":"of the other social safety nets."},{"time":13254,"text":"They can't contain them, so we must."},{"time":15587,"text":"That's our job:"},{"time":17030,"text":"contain them, control them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20137,"text":"Over the years, as a prison system,"},{"time":22594,"text":"as a nation, and as a society,"},{"time":24415,"text":"we've become very good at that,"},{"time":25890,"text":"but that shouldn't make you happy."},{"time":28010,"text":"Today we incarcerate more people per capita"},{"time":29710,"text":"than any other country in the world."},{"time":31847,"text":"We have more black men in prison today"},{"time":33760,"text":"than were under slavery in 1850."},{"time":36321,"text":"We house the parents of almost three million"},{"time":38081,"text":"of our community's children,"},{"time":39805,"text":"and we've become the new asylum,"},{"time":41825,"text":"the largest mental health provider in this nation."},{"time":44862,"text":"When we lock someone up,"},{"time":46333,"text":"that is no small thing."},{"time":47964,"text":"And yet, we are called the\nDepartment of Corrections."},{"time":51122,"text":"Today I want to talk about"},{"time":52510,"text":"changing the way we think about corrections."},{"time":54605,"text":"I believe, and my experience tells me,"},{"time":56664,"text":"that when we change the way we think,"},{"time":58373,"text":"we create new possibilities, or futures,"},{"time":61207,"text":"and prisons need a different future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63833,"text":"I've spent my entire career\nin corrections, over 30 years."},{"time":67305,"text":"I followed my dad into this field."},{"time":68785,"text":"He was a Vietnam veteran. Corrections suited him."},{"time":71930,"text":"He was strong, steady, disciplined."},{"time":74940,"text":"I was not so much any of those things,"},{"time":76380,"text":"and I'm sure that worried him about me."},{"time":78779,"text":"Eventually I decided, if I was\ngoing to end up in prison,"},{"time":81622,"text":"I'd better end up on the right side of the bars,"},{"time":82943,"text":"so I thought I'd check it out,"},{"time":84650,"text":"take a tour of the place my dad worked,"},{"time":86920,"text":"the McNeil Island Penitentiary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89101,"text":"Now this was the early '80s,"},{"time":90811,"text":"and prisons weren't quite what you see"},{"time":92338,"text":"on TV or in the movies."},{"time":94320,"text":"In many ways, it was worse."},{"time":96840,"text":"I walked into a cell house that was five tiers high."},{"time":99454,"text":"There were eight men to a cell."},{"time":101079,"text":"there were 550 men in that living unit."},{"time":103427,"text":"And just in case you wondered,"},{"time":105310,"text":"they shared one toilet in those small confines."},{"time":108376,"text":"An officer put a key in a lockbox,"},{"time":109879,"text":"and hundreds of men streamed out of their cells."},{"time":112421,"text":"Hundreds of men streamed out of their cells."},{"time":114400,"text":"I walked away as fast as I could."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116763,"text":"Eventually I went back and\nI started as an officer there."},{"time":119361,"text":"My job was to run one of those cell blocks"},{"time":121158,"text":"and to control those hundreds of men."},{"time":124319,"text":"When I went to work at our receptions center,"},{"time":126164,"text":"I could actually hear the inmates \nroiling from the parking lot,"},{"time":128890,"text":"shaking cell doors, yelling,"},{"time":131384,"text":"tearing up their cells."},{"time":133058,"text":"Take hundreds of volatile people and lock them up,"},{"time":135422,"text":"and what you get is chaos."},{"time":137186,"text":"Contain and control â€” that was our job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139959,"text":"One way we learned to do this more effectively"},{"time":142280,"text":"was a new type of housing unit"},{"time":143490,"text":"called the Intensive Management Unit, IMU,"},{"time":146193,"text":"a modern version of a \"hole.\""},{"time":148016,"text":"We put inmates in cells behind solid steel doors"},{"time":150538,"text":"with cuff ports so we could restrain them"},{"time":152819,"text":"and feed them."},{"time":154160,"text":"Guess what?"},{"time":156497,"text":"It got quieter."},{"time":157991,"text":"Disturbances died down in the general population."},{"time":160488,"text":"Places became safer"},{"time":161839,"text":"because those inmates who\nwere most violent or disruptive"},{"time":164439,"text":"could now be isolated."},{"time":165864,"text":"But isolation isn't good."},{"time":167595,"text":"Deprive people of social\ncontact and they deteriorate."},{"time":170424,"text":"It was hard getting them out of IMU,"},{"time":172359,"text":"for them and for us."},{"time":174912,"text":"Even in prison, it's no small thing"},{"time":177381,"text":"to lock someone up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179367,"text":"My next assignment was to one\nof the state's deep-end prisons"},{"time":181921,"text":"where some of our more violent\nor disruptive inmates are housed."},{"time":184856,"text":"By then, the industry had advanced a lot,"},{"time":186700,"text":"and we had different tools and techniques"},{"time":188758,"text":"to manage disruptive behavior."},{"time":190795,"text":"We had beanbag guns and pepper spray"},{"time":193020,"text":"and plexiglass shields,"},{"time":194910,"text":"flash bangs, emergency response teams."},{"time":197345,"text":"We met violence with force"},{"time":199209,"text":"and chaos with chaos."},{"time":200670,"text":"We were pretty good at putting out fires."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203197,"text":"While I was there, I met two\nexperienced correctional workers"},{"time":206498,"text":"who were also researchers,"},{"time":208034,"text":"an anthropologist and a sociologist."},{"time":211225,"text":"One day, one of them commented to me and said,"},{"time":212775,"text":"\"You know, you're pretty good at putting out fires."},{"time":214813,"text":"Have you ever thought about how to prevent them?\""},{"time":218647,"text":"I was patient with them,"},{"time":220624,"text":"explaining our brute force approach"},{"time":221933,"text":"to making prisons safer."},{"time":223790,"text":"They were patient with me."},{"time":225324,"text":"Out of those conversations grew some new ideas"},{"time":227501,"text":"and we started some small experiments."},{"time":229397,"text":"First, we started training our officers in teams"},{"time":231798,"text":"rather than sending them one or two\nat a time to the state training academy."},{"time":235040,"text":"Instead of four weeks of training, we gave them 10."},{"time":237350,"text":"Then we experimented with an apprenticeship model"},{"time":239627,"text":"where we paired new staff with veteran staff."},{"time":243200,"text":"They both got better at the work."},{"time":245713,"text":"Second, we added verbal de-escalation skills"},{"time":248323,"text":"into the training continuum"},{"time":250213,"text":"and made it part of the use of force continuum."},{"time":252950,"text":"It was the non-force use of force."},{"time":255434,"text":"And then we did something even more radical."},{"time":257036,"text":"We trained the inmates on those same skills."},{"time":259346,"text":"We changed the skill set,"},{"time":261642,"text":"reducing violence, not just responding to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264813,"text":"Third, when we expanded our facility, \nwe tried a new type of design."},{"time":268047,"text":"Now the biggest and most controversial component"},{"time":270752,"text":"of this design, of course, was the toilet."},{"time":274429,"text":"There were no toilets."},{"time":276118,"text":"Now that might not sound\nsignificant to you here today,"},{"time":278749,"text":"but at the time, it was huge."},{"time":280134,"text":"No one had ever heard of a cell without a toilet."},{"time":282247,"text":"We all thought it was dangerous and crazy."},{"time":284495,"text":"Even eight men to a cell had a toilet."},{"time":287602,"text":"That small detail changed the way we worked."},{"time":290459,"text":"Inmates and staff started interacting"},{"time":292189,"text":"more often and openly and developing a rapport."},{"time":295463,"text":"It was easier to detect conflict and intervene"},{"time":297296,"text":"before it escalated."},{"time":298610,"text":"The unit was cleaner, quieter,\nsafer and more humane."},{"time":302246,"text":"This was more effective at keeping the peace"},{"time":304451,"text":"than any intimidation technique I'd seen to that point."},{"time":307960,"text":"Interacting changes the way you behave,"},{"time":309388,"text":"both for the officer and the inmate."},{"time":311494,"text":"We changed the environment\nand we changed the behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314644,"text":"Now, just in case I hadn't learned this lesson,"},{"time":316537,"text":"they assigned me to headquarters next,"},{"time":318947,"text":"and that's where I ran straight\nup against system change."},{"time":321473,"text":"Now, many things work against system change:"},{"time":324042,"text":"politics and politicians, bills and laws,"},{"time":326151,"text":"courts and lawsuits, internal politics."},{"time":328919,"text":"System change is difficult and slow,"},{"time":330989,"text":"and oftentimes it doesn't take you"},{"time":332531,"text":"where you want to go."},{"time":334214,"text":"It's no small thing to change a prison system."},{"time":338236,"text":"So what I did do is I reflected\non my earlier experiences"},{"time":340910,"text":"and I remembered that when we interacted\nwith offenders, the heat went down."},{"time":344164,"text":"When we changed the environment,\nthe behavior changed."},{"time":346155,"text":"And these were not huge system changes."},{"time":347944,"text":"These were small changes, and these changes"},{"time":349699,"text":"created new possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351910,"text":"So next, I got reassigned as\nsuperintendent of a small prison."},{"time":354617,"text":"And at the same time, I was working on my degree"},{"time":356876,"text":"at the Evergreen State College."},{"time":358957,"text":"I interacted with a lot of\npeople who were not like me,"},{"time":360950,"text":"people who had different ideas"},{"time":362320,"text":"and came from different backgrounds."},{"time":364026,"text":"One of them was a rainforest ecologist."},{"time":366622,"text":"She looked at my small prison and what she saw"},{"time":368372,"text":"was a laboratory."},{"time":370158,"text":"We talked and discovered how prisons and inmates"},{"time":373083,"text":"could actually help advance science"},{"time":375115,"text":"by helping them complete projects"},{"time":376744,"text":"they couldn't complete on their own,"},{"time":378555,"text":"like repopulating endangered species:"},{"time":380873,"text":"frogs, butterflies, endangered prairie plants."},{"time":384020,"text":"At the same time, we found ways to make"},{"time":385347,"text":"our operation more efficient"},{"time":386930,"text":"through the addition of solar power,"},{"time":389153,"text":"rainwater catchment, organic gardening, recycling."},{"time":392683,"text":"This initiative has led to many projects"},{"time":395182,"text":"that have had huge system-wide impact,"},{"time":396884,"text":"not just in our system, but in \nother state systems as well,"},{"time":400227,"text":"small experiments making a big difference"},{"time":402423,"text":"to science, to the community."},{"time":405475,"text":"The way we think about our work changes our work."},{"time":408642,"text":"The project just made my job\nmore interesting and exciting."},{"time":411823,"text":"I was excited. Staff were excited."},{"time":413780,"text":"Officers were excited. Inmates were excited."},{"time":415790,"text":"They were inspired."},{"time":417543,"text":"Everybody wanted to be part of this."},{"time":419099,"text":"They were making a contribution, a difference,"},{"time":421418,"text":"one they thought was meaningful and important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423657,"text":"Let me be clear on what's going on here, though."},{"time":425513,"text":"Inmates are highly adaptive."},{"time":427256,"text":"They have to be."},{"time":428928,"text":"Oftentimes, they know more about our own systems"},{"time":431689,"text":"than the people who run them."},{"time":433670,"text":"And they're here for a reason."},{"time":435321,"text":"I don't see my job as to punish them or forgive them,"},{"time":438607,"text":"but I do think they can have"},{"time":439870,"text":"decent and meaningful lives even in prison."},{"time":442623,"text":"So that was the question:"},{"time":444200,"text":"Could inmates live decent and meaningful lives,"},{"time":447380,"text":"and if so, what difference would that make?"},{"time":450650,"text":"So I took that question back to the deep end,"},{"time":453547,"text":"where some of our most\nviolent offenders are housed."},{"time":456212,"text":"Remember, IMUs are for punishment."},{"time":457843,"text":"You don't get perks there, like programming."},{"time":459907,"text":"That was how we thought."},{"time":461837,"text":"But then we started to realize that if any inmates"},{"time":463950,"text":"needed programming, it\nwas these particular inmates."},{"time":466237,"text":"In fact, they needed intensive programming."},{"time":468423,"text":"So we changed our thinking 180 degrees,"},{"time":470761,"text":"and we started looking for new possibilities."},{"time":473124,"text":"What we found was a new kind of chair."},{"time":475662,"text":"Instead of using the chair for punishment,"},{"time":477608,"text":"we put it in classrooms."},{"time":479278,"text":"Okay, we didn't forget our responsibility to control,"},{"time":482330,"text":"but now inmates could interact safely, face-to-face"},{"time":484559,"text":"with other inmates and staff,"},{"time":486205,"text":"and because control was no longer an issue,"},{"time":487840,"text":"everybody could focus on other things,"},{"time":490130,"text":"like learning. Behavior changed."},{"time":492772,"text":"We changed our thinking, and we changed \nwhat was possible, and this gives me hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497607,"text":"Now, I can't tell you that any of this stuff will work."},{"time":500143,"text":"What I can tell you, though, it is working."},{"time":502735,"text":"Our prisons are getting safer\nfor both staff and inmates,"},{"time":506164,"text":"and when our prisons are safe,"},{"time":507558,"text":"we can put our energies into\na lot more than just controlling."},{"time":511013,"text":"Reducing recidivism may be our ultimate goal,"},{"time":513295,"text":"but it's not our only goal."},{"time":514970,"text":"To be honest with you, preventing crime"},{"time":516726,"text":"takes so much more from so many more people"},{"time":518695,"text":"and institutions."},{"time":520208,"text":"If we rely on just prisons to reduce crime,"},{"time":523476,"text":"I'm afraid we'll never get there."},{"time":525434,"text":"But prisons can do some things"},{"time":527289,"text":"we never thought they could do."},{"time":528965,"text":"Prisons can be the source of innovation"},{"time":531000,"text":"and sustainability,"},{"time":532381,"text":"repopulating endangered species\nand environmental restoration."},{"time":535740,"text":"Inmates can be scientists and beekeepers,"},{"time":538385,"text":"dog rescuers."},{"time":540145,"text":"Prisons can be the source of meaningful work"},{"time":542678,"text":"and opportunity for staff"},{"time":544635,"text":"and the inmates who live there."},{"time":546976,"text":"We can contain and control"},{"time":549150,"text":"and provide humane environments."},{"time":551273,"text":"These are not opposing qualities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553864,"text":"We can't wait 10 to 20 years to find out"},{"time":556165,"text":"if this is worth doing."},{"time":557752,"text":"Our strategy is not massive system change."},{"time":560446,"text":"Our strategy is hundreds of small changes"},{"time":562250,"text":"that take place in days or months, not years."},{"time":565935,"text":"We need more small pilots where we learn as we go,"},{"time":569332,"text":"pilots that change the range of possibility."},{"time":572333,"text":"We need new and better ways to measure impacts"},{"time":574422,"text":"on engagement, on interaction,"},{"time":576163,"text":"on safe environments."},{"time":578179,"text":"We need more opportunities to participate in"},{"time":580499,"text":"and contribute to our communities,"},{"time":582671,"text":"your communities."},{"time":585120,"text":"Prisons need to be secure, yes, safe, yes."},{"time":588164,"text":"We can do that."},{"time":589147,"text":"Prisons need to provide humane environments"},{"time":591168,"text":"where people can participate, contribute,"},{"time":593235,"text":"and learn meaningful lives."},{"time":594921,"text":"We're learning how to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596770,"text":"That's why I'm hopeful."},{"time":598220,"text":"We don't have to stay stuck\nin old ideas about prison."},{"time":600511,"text":"We can define that. We can create that."},{"time":602975,"text":"And when we do that thoughtfully and with humanity,"},{"time":605425,"text":"prisons can be more than the bucket"},{"time":607362,"text":"for failed social policy."},{"time":608951,"text":"Maybe finally, we will earn our title:"},{"time":612301,"text":"a department of corrections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614296,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616396,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}